{"id":812,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":177,"title":"Cam9 - Test 1 - Part 1","subtitle":"Job Inquiry Phone Call","level":"B1","parts":83,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam9-test-1-part-1.812/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/0-ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1.mp3","transcript":"Good evening. King's Restaurant.\nGood evening.\nI'm ringing about the job I understand you have vacant.\nOh yes.\nI'd like to find out a few more details, if i may.\nYes, of course. Can i take your name?\nIt's Peter Chin.\nOkay Peter.\nWell, if you want to ask about the job and then if we're both still interested,\nwe could arrange for you to come for an interview.\nGreat, thanks.\nI'm afraid i missed the advert for the job but heard about it from a friend.\nThat's no problem at all.\nWhat would you like to know?\nWell, um, what sort of work is it? Washing up?\nIt's answering the phone.\nOh, right, fine.\nAnd not waiting at table.\nThat'd be good.\nAnd how many nights a week would it be?\nWell, we're really only busy at the weekend.\nSo two nights?\nThree actually, so it would work out at twelve hours a week.\nThat'd be fine.\nIt wouldn't interfere with my studies.\nAre you at the university?\nYes. First year Physics student.\nOh right.\nUm, and because I'm not an EU national, would I need a work permit?\nYes you would.\nJust get your tutor to sign it.\nThat wouldn't be a problem, if i were to get the job.\nUm, where exactly is the restaurant?\nWell, we have two branches -\nthe one we're recruiting for is in Hillsdunne Road.\nI don't know that.\nHow do you spell it please?\nIt's HILLSDUNNE Road.\nGot that. Thanks.\nis it near a bus stop?\nYes. The nearest one would probably be just beside the library.\nOh yes, I know it. That'd be fine for me.\nAnd could I ask about the pay?\nWe're offering £4.45 an hour.\nThat's very good.\nMy last job was £3.95 an hour.\nWe feel it's pretty good and we also offer some good fringe benefits.\nReally?\nWell, we give you a free dinner, so you eat well.\nRight, better than hostel food!\nWe certainly hope so!\nAnd we also offer extra pay for working on national holidays.\nOh, that's a really good perk, isn't it?\nYes, we think so.\nAnd then because of the difficulties of getting public transport,\nif you're working after 11 o'clock we drive you home.\nOh, that's good to know.\nWell, we'd certainly be interested in inviting you for an interview, if you're still interested?\nOh yes, certainly.\nCould I just also ask what qualities you're looking for?\nWell, for this particular job we want a clear voice, which you obviously do have!\nThanks.\nAnd you must be able to think quickly, you know.\nWell, I hope I'd...\nSo, when could you come in for an interview?\nWe're actually quite quiet tonight?\nSorry, I couldn't come tonight...\nor tomorrow, I'm afraid.\nThursday's okay, that'd be 22nd of October.\nFine, after 5 p.m?\nYes, fine. Would 6 o'clock be okay?\nPerfect.\nAnd could you bring along the names of two referees?\nYes, that's fine, no problem.\nGood, I look forward to seeing you.\nOh, by the way, who should i ask for?\nOh yes, of course, sorry.\nMy name is Samira Manuja.\nCan you spell that, please?\nMANUJA.\nOkay.\nI've got that. Thanks very much.\nLook forward to seeing you later on then.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:50:55","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Good evening. King's Restaurant.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/1.mp3","time_start":2.5,"time_end":4.47},{"position":2,"content":"Good evening.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/2.mp3","time_start":4.47,"time_end":5.64},{"position":3,"content":"I'm ringing about the job I understand you have vacant.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/3.mp3","time_start":5.64,"time_end":9.19},{"position":4,"content":"Oh yes.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/4.mp3","time_start":9.19,"time_end":10.03},{"position":5,"content":"I'd like to find out a few more details, if i may.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/5.mp3","time_start":10.03,"time_end":12.9},{"position":6,"content":"Yes, of course. Can i take your name?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/6.mp3","time_start":12.9,"time_end":14.99},{"position":7,"content":"It's Peter Chin.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/7.mp3","time_start":14.99,"time_end":16.9},{"position":8,"content":"Okay Peter.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/8.mp3","time_start":16.9,"time_end":18.68},{"position":9,"content":"Well, if you want to ask about the job and then if we're both still interested,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/9.mp3","time_start":18.68,"time_end":22.92},{"position":10,"content":"we could arrange for you to come for an interview.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/10.mp3","time_start":22.92,"time_end":26.03},{"position":11,"content":"Great, thanks.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/11.mp3","time_start":26.03,"time_end":27.64},{"position":12,"content":"I'm afraid i missed the advert for the job but heard about it from a friend.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/12.mp3","time_start":27.64,"time_end":32.06},{"position":13,"content":"That's no problem at all.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/13.mp3","time_start":32.06,"time_end":33.5},{"position":14,"content":"What would you like to know?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/14.mp3","time_start":33.5,"time_end":34.87},{"position":15,"content":"Well, um, what sort of work is it? Washing up?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/15.mp3","time_start":34.87,"time_end":39.36},{"position":16,"content":"It's answering the phone.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/16.mp3","time_start":39.36,"time_end":41.26},{"position":17,"content":"Oh, right, fine.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/17.mp3","time_start":41.26,"time_end":43.72},{"position":18,"content":"And not waiting at table.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/18.mp3","time_start":43.72,"time_end":46.35},{"position":19,"content":"That'd be good.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/19.mp3","time_start":46.35,"time_end":47.96},{"position":20,"content":"And how many nights a week would it be?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/20.mp3","time_start":47.96,"time_end":50.66},{"position":21,"content":"Well, we're really only busy at the weekend.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/21.mp3","time_start":50.66,"time_end":53.67},{"position":22,"content":"So two nights?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/22.mp3","time_start":53.67,"time_end":55.12},{"position":23,"content":"Three actually, so it would work out at twelve hours a week.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/23.mp3","time_start":55.12,"time_end":59.12},{"position":24,"content":"That'd be fine.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/24.mp3","time_start":59.12,"time_end":60.35},{"position":25,"content":"It wouldn't interfere with my studies.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/25.mp3","time_start":60.35,"time_end":62.48},{"position":26,"content":"Are you at the university?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/26.mp3","time_start":62.48,"time_end":63.9},{"position":27,"content":"Yes. First year Physics student.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/27.mp3","time_start":63.9,"time_end":66.18},{"position":28,"content":"Oh right.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/28.mp3","time_start":66.18,"time_end":67.24},{"position":29,"content":"Um, and because I'm not an EU national, would I need a work permit?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/29.mp3","time_start":67.24,"time_end":72.58},{"position":30,"content":"Yes you would.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/30.mp3","time_start":72.58,"time_end":73.91},{"position":31,"content":"Just get your tutor to sign it.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/31.mp3","time_start":73.91,"time_end":75.71},{"position":32,"content":"That wouldn't be a problem, if i were to get the job.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/32.mp3","time_start":75.71,"time_end":78.56},{"position":33,"content":"Um, where exactly is the restaurant?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/33.mp3","time_start":78.56,"time_end":82.28},{"position":34,"content":"Well, we have two branches -","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/34.mp3","time_start":82.28,"time_end":84.27},{"position":35,"content":"the one we're recruiting for is in Hillsdunne Road.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/35.mp3","time_start":84.27,"time_end":88.19},{"position":36,"content":"I don't know that.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/36.mp3","time_start":88.19,"time_end":90.16},{"position":37,"content":"How do you spell it please?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/37.mp3","time_start":90.16,"time_end":92.15},{"position":38,"content":"It's HILLSDUNNE Road.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/38.mp3","time_start":92.15,"time_end":98.64},{"position":39,"content":"Got that. Thanks.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/39.mp3","time_start":99.58,"time_end":101.58},{"position":40,"content":"is it near a bus stop?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/40.mp3","time_start":101.83,"time_end":103.51},{"position":41,"content":"Yes. The nearest one would probably be just beside the library.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/41.mp3","time_start":103.51,"time_end":107.4},{"position":42,"content":"Oh yes, I know it. That'd be fine for me.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/42.mp3","time_start":107.4,"time_end":110.82},{"position":43,"content":"And could I ask about the pay?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/43.mp3","time_start":110.82,"time_end":113.32},{"position":44,"content":"We're offering £4.45 an hour.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/44.mp3","time_start":113.32,"time_end":116.47},{"position":45,"content":"That's very good.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/45.mp3","time_start":116.47,"time_end":117.72},{"position":46,"content":"My last job was £3.95 an hour.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/46.mp3","time_start":117.72,"time_end":120.71},{"position":47,"content":"We feel it's pretty good and we also offer some good fringe benefits.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/47.mp3","time_start":121.51,"time_end":125.54},{"position":48,"content":"Really?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/48.mp3","time_start":125.54,"time_end":126.39},{"position":49,"content":"Well, we give you a free dinner, so you eat well.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/49.mp3","time_start":126.39,"time_end":129.72},{"position":50,"content":"Right, better than hostel food!","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/50.mp3","time_start":129.72,"time_end":132.11},{"position":51,"content":"We certainly hope so!","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/51.mp3","time_start":132.11,"time_end":133.94},{"position":52,"content":"And we also offer extra pay for working on national holidays.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/52.mp3","time_start":133.94,"time_end":137.47},{"position":53,"content":"Oh, that's a really good perk, isn't it?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/53.mp3","time_start":137.47,"time_end":139.82},{"position":54,"content":"Yes, we think so.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/54.mp3","time_start":139.82,"time_end":141.2},{"position":55,"content":"And then because of the difficulties of getting public transport,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/55.mp3","time_start":141.2,"time_end":144.5},{"position":56,"content":"if you're working after 11 o'clock we drive you home.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-9-test-1-part-1-2023-07-22-18-07-21/56.mp3","time_start":144.5,"time_end":147.4},{"position":57,"content":"Oh, that's good to know.","audio_url":"h